    <h2>1. General Safety Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>All pet products sold by GetPawsy are intended for use under adult supervision. While we strive to offer safe, high-quality products, no toy or accessory is completely indestructible or risk-free. Pet owners assume full responsibility for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Selecting appropriate products for their pet's size, breed, and temperament</li>
      <li>Supervising their pet during product use</li>
      <li>Regular inspection of products for wear and damage</li>
      <li>Proper use of products as intended</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Supervision Requirements</h2>
    <div class="warning-box">
      <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è ALWAYS SUPERVISE YOUR PET</strong></p>
      <p>Never leave your pet unattended with any toy, chew, or accessory. Even products designed for heavy chewers can be damaged and pose risks if left unsupervised. Supervision is especially critical for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Aggressive chewers</li>
        <li>Puppies and kittens</li>
        <li>Senior pets with dental issues</li>
        <li>Pets with known behavioral issues</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>3. Size Appropriateness Guidelines</h2>
    <p>Selecting the right size product is critical for safety:</p>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Pet Size</th>
        <th>Recommended Product Size</th>
        <th>Risk If Wrong Size</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Small (under 20 lbs)</td>
        <td>Small / XS products</td>
        <td>Large products may be too heavy or cause injury</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Medium (20-50 lbs)</td>
        <td>Medium products</td>
        <td>Small products pose choking hazards</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Large (50-90 lbs)</td>
        <td>Large / XL products</td>
        <td>Small/medium products can be swallowed or cause choking</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Giant (90+ lbs)</td>
        <td>XL / Giant products only</td>
        <td>Smaller products are serious choking/ingestion hazards</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h2>4. Risks Associated with Pet Toys</h2>
    <p>Pet owners should be aware of the following potential risks:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Choking:</strong> Small parts or pieces that break off can be swallowed</li>
      <li><strong>Intestinal Blockage:</strong> Ingested materials can cause serious digestive issues</li>
      <li><strong>Dental Damage:</strong> Hard toys may crack or damage teeth</li>
      <li><strong>Strangulation:</strong> Ropes, strings, and straps can wrap around necks</li>
      <li><strong>Allergic Reactions:</strong> Some pets may be allergic to certain materials</li>
      <li><strong>Eye or Ear Injury:</strong> Rigid or pointed objects can cause injury during play</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Product Inspection Guidelines</h2>
    <div class="safety-tips">
      <p><strong>‚úì Before Each Use, Check For:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Loose parts, stitching, or stuffing</li>
        <li>Cracks, tears, or holes</li>
        <li>Worn or frayed materials</li>
        <li>Damaged squeakers or noise makers</li>
        <li>Sharp edges or points</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Immediately discard any product showing signs of damage.</strong></p>
    </div>

